<div id="review_1536188771" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1536188771" />
    <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock"><img alt="Scott  Hitchcock" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459187975p2/50894754.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1536188771?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Scott  Hitchcock" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Scott  Hitchcock" href="/user/show/50894754-scott-hitchcock">Scott  Hitchcock</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6569831-furies-of-calderon">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50894754-scott-hitchcock?shelf=butcher">butcher</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1536188771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12933649450353340771">I did this one as an audio book with Kate Reading as the narrator. She was excellent as always. <br/><br/>Much like in Wheel of Time there is a discipline collar similar to the A&apos;Dam. For whatever reason these get a rise out of me worse than any of the other evil things in books much darker than this or WOT. There&apos;s just something so wrong about being able to throw a collar around a person&apos;s neck and controlling them against their will. <br/><br/>I liked but didn&apos;t love the characters and found Tavi and Isana to bo</span>
  <span id="freeText12933649450353340771" style="display:none">I did this one as an audio book with Kate Reading as the narrator. She was excellent as always. <br /><br />Much like in Wheel of Time there is a discipline collar similar to the A'Dam. For whatever reason these get a rise out of me worse than any of the other evil things in books much darker than this or WOT. There's just something so wrong about being able to throw a collar around a person's neck and controlling them against their will. <br /><br />I liked but didn't love the characters and found Tavi and Isana to both be a bit whiny. There also wasn't that one thing that stood out to make the book unique. <br /><br />I do feel it has potential as the series grows so I will continue with it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12933649450353340771" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


